PRECISION DIMENSIONLESS CONSTANTS: THE HARD SCIENCES
===========================================================================

CATEGORY 1: TURBULENCE / FLUID MECHANICS

| Constant                  | Value         | Precision | Derived? |
|---------------------------|---------------|-----------|----------|
| von Kármán κ              | 0.40 ± 0.02   | 5%        | NO       |
| Kolmogorov C_K            | 1.5 ± 0.1     | 7%        | NO       |
| Smagorinsky C_S           | 0.1-0.2       | ~50%      | NO       |
| Re_crit (pipe)            | ~2300         | ~10%      | NO       |
| Re_crit (flat plate)      | ~5×10⁵        | ~20%      | NO       |
| Drag coeff sphere Re=0    | 24/Re (exact) | exact     | YES      |
| Stokes drag               | 6π (exact)    | exact     | YES      |

  VERDICT: Too imprecise for PSLQ (need 10+ digits).
  The unexplained constants (κ, C_K, Re_crit) are known
  to only 2-3 significant figures. Can't test meaningfully.

CATEGORY 2: CHEMISTRY / MOLECULAR SPECTROSCOPY

| Constant                        | Value              | Precision | Derived from   |
|---------------------------------|--------------------|-----------|----------------|
| H₂ dissociation energy          | 36118.0696(4) cm⁻¹| 1.1e-8    | α, m_e/m_p     |
| H₂ vibration freq ν₁            | 4161.166 cm⁻¹     | 1e-6      | α, m_e/m_p     |
| CO rotation const B₀            | 57635.968 MHz      | 1e-7      | α, m_e/m_p,m_C |
| N₂ dissociation                 | 78714 cm⁻¹         | ~0.01%    | α, nuclear     |

  VERDICT: High precision available but all DERIVED from α and
  nuclear masses. These don't contain new free parameters.
  Testing them tests many-body quantum chemistry, not SM constants.

