CATEGORY 5: COSMOLOGY

| Constant                  | Value           | Precision | Free param? |
|---------------------------|-----------------|-----------|-------------|
| Hubble H₀                | 67.4 ± 0.5 km/s/Mpc| 0.7%   | YES         |
| CMB temperature T₀       | 2.72548 ± 0.00057 K| 0.02%   | YES         |
| Baryon density Ω_b h²    | 0.02237 ± 0.00015 | 0.7%    | YES         |
| DM density Ω_c h²        | 0.1200 ± 0.0012   | 1%      | YES         |
| Spectral index n_s       | 0.9649 ± 0.0042   | 0.4%    | YES         |
| Amplitude ln(10¹⁰A_s)   | 3.044 ± 0.014     | 0.5%    | YES         |

  VERDICT: These ARE free parameters (cosmological, not SM).
  Precision: 2-4 significant figures. Marginal for PSLQ.
  But Ω_c h² = 0.1200 ± 0.0012 is suspiciously close to α_s!

  Ω_c h² = 0.12
  α_s    = 0.118
  Ratio: 1.016949
  Difference: 0.0020
  Both ~0.12. Coincidence at 2% level. Not meaningful
  without a physical mechanism linking DM density to QCD.

